doc.after: The peregrine falcon lives mostly along mountain ranges river valleys coastlines and increasingly in cities 11 In mild winter regions it is usually a permanent resident and some individuals especially adult males will remain on the breeding territory Only populations that breed in Arctic climates typically migrate great distances during the northern winter 47
